xmds-extended
=============

This repository is an unofficial derivative of XMDS2 for continued development and practical use.

Original XMDS2 project:

- Project page: https://sourceforge.net/projects/xmds/
- Documentation: https://xmds.sourceforge.net/

This repository preserves the original XMDS2 licensing and copyright notices.
Please see `COPYING` and `COPYRIGHT` for the governing terms.

Current work in this repository includes:

- native Windows compatibility without MSYS or WSL
- build and runtime fixes for modern Python and native Windows toolchains
- regression test and validation improvements
- room for further local extensions and downstream development

Status
------

The current codebase has been validated for native Windows use, including:

- successful compilation with `python bin\xmds2 examples\lorenz.xmds`
- successful execution with `.\lorenz.cmd`
- regression groups run individually from native PowerShell
- rerun of a user example with numerically consistent results relative to prior Linux output

Documentation
-------------

Additional documentation prepared in this repository includes:

- `docs/windows-native-guide-zh.md`
- `contrib/windows-native-release-kit/`

Notes
-----

- This is not the official XMDS2 repository.
- XMDS2 remains the upstream project and the original codebase is credited to its original authors.
- If you need official project information, please refer to the upstream SourceForge pages above.
